Enum AccessLevel

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<AccessLevel>
      • model.AccessLevel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<AccessLevel>, java.util.Comparator<AccessLevel>

    public enum AccessLevel
extends java.lang.Enum<AccessLevel>
implements java.util.Comparator<AccessLevel>
    AccessLevel is an Enum to enumerate the hierarchy of access levels particular Users have for particular Conferences. The access levels vary in number between integers 0 and 2 but have been described here as enumerations for code readability.
    Version:
    2 June 2014
    Author:
    Trevor Jennings
